class Solution:
    def minRemoveToMakeValid(self, s: str) -> str:
        # Stack to keep track of indices of '('
        stack = []
        # List to keep track of characters to remove
        remove = set()

        # First pass to find unmatched ')'
        for i, char in enumerate(s):
            if char == '(':
                stack.append(i)
            elif char == ')':
                if stack:
                    stack.pop()
                else:
                    remove.add(i)

        # Add remaining unmatched '(' to the remove set
        remove.update(stack)

        # Build the result string excluding the characters in the remove set
        result = []
        for i, char in enumerate(s):
            if i not in remove:
                result.append(char)

        return ''.join(result)
```

This solution uses a stack to track the indices of the '(' characters and a set to track the indices of characters that need to be removed. In the first pass, it identifies unmatched ')' and adds them to the remove set. After that, any remaining indices in the stack are unmatched '(', which are also added to the remove set. Finally, it constructs the result string by excluding the characters at the indices in the remove set.
